member.name: M:SWIFTFramework.SwiftParser.GetMessageAsXml(SWIFTFramework.SwiftMessage)
member.summary: Returns the message in the XML format. The message is serialized with its complete structure, SWIFT tags are divided into sequences and each XML tag is named according to the type-dependent object model. Only the messages with a structure fully corresponding to the appropriate type definition can be serialized by this method. Otherwise the InvalidOperationException is thrown.

member.name: M:SWIFTFramework.SwiftParser.GetMessageAsXmlRaw(SWIFTFramework.SwiftMessage)
member.summary: Returns the message in the XML format where only the Blocks and SWIFT Tags are serialized. It does not take the message type into account, therefore the type-dependent object model built upon the message is ignored. Even the messages with an invalid structure can be serialized by this method.
